# Cursor Rules Compatibility Bridge

Primary Cursor guidance now lives in [`.cursor/rules/`](.cursor/rules/).

## Read first

1. [`.cursor/rules/README.md`](.cursor/rules/README.md)
2. [`.cursor/rules/00-entrypoint.mdc`](.cursor/rules/00-entrypoint.mdc)
3. [`.github/copilot-instructions.md`](.github/copilot-instructions.md)
4. [`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md)
5. Binding rules:
   - [`docs/rules/architecture-protocol.md`](docs/rules/architecture-protocol.md)
   - [`docs/rules/transactions.md`](docs/rules/transactions.md)
   - [`docs/rules/resilience.md`](docs/rules/resilience.md)
   - [`docs/rules/sql.md`](docs/rules/sql.md)
   - [`docs/rules/mapping.md`](docs/rules/mapping.md)
   - [`docs/rules/code-quality.md`](docs/rules/code-quality.md)
   - [`docs/rules/testing.md`](docs/rules/testing.md)
6. Pattern sources:
   - [`templates/`](templates/)
   - [`docs/starter-pack/shadow-examples/`](docs/starter-pack/shadow-examples/)
7. Manual workflow rules:
   - [`.cursor/rules/refactor-uow.mdc`](.cursor/rules/refactor-uow.mdc)
   - [`.cursor/rules/add-resilience.mdc`](.cursor/rules/add-resilience.mdc)
   - [`.cursor/rules/api-standard.mdc`](.cursor/rules/api-standard.mdc)

## Notes

- Treat this file as a legacy compatibility entrypoint only. Keep the stable, versioned Cursor guidance under `.cursor/rules/` first, then mirror here only when older consumers still require it.
- Toggle behaviour modes via [`.ai-modes`](.ai-modes) when present.
- If a feature spec exists under `docs/specs/`, it overrides defaults.
